c href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=122574"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="122575">(D) Maximal individual codon coverage over the expected coverage for all translated transcripts of <em>Arabidopsis</em>. Vertical lines indicate the strength of stalling sites of <em>shGAG</em> in the WT or <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1026092230sd" type="geneprod" role="component"><em>rdr6</em></sd-pretag> background. Percentages specify the proportion of transcripts with more pronounced stalling events than <em>shGAG</em>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=122575"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="122576">(E) Overlay between <em><sd-pretag id="sdPretag1923882706sd" type="molecule" role="reporter">35S</sd-pretag>:<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1980039113sd" parent-tag-id="40">EVD</sd-pretag></em> siRNAs (red) and RIBO-seq profiles (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1253075796sd" type="geneprod" role="component">black</sd-pretag>) in the WT background. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=122576"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="122577">(F) Schematic representation of putative ribosome stalling-linked <sd-pretag id="sdPretag686021163sd" type="molecule" role="component">mRNA</sd-pretag> breakage generating 5'OH ends. Lack of 5'PO<sub>4</sub> prevents XRN 5'-&gt;3' exonucleolytic activity (see Fig.6A), granting the RNA to be used as template by <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1137736763sd" type="geneprod" role="component">RDR6</sd-pretag>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=122577"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="122578">(G) Overlap between ribosomal footprints and mapping of 5'OH ends from <em><sd-pretag id="sdPretag432614665sd" type="molecule" role="reporter">35S</sd-pretag>:<sd-pretag id="sdPretag469388560sd" parent-tag-id="40">EVD</sd-pretag></em> in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1649643037sd" type="geneprod" role="component"><em>rdr6</em></sd-pretag> cloned through RtbC ligation. Regions investigated are highlighted in grey. 5'OH ends were only successfully cloned from region #1. Alignment of sequenced clones to <sd-pretag id="sdPretag938534023sd" parent-tag-id="40"><em>EVD</em></sd-pretag> is displayed in Appendix Fig. S9. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=122578"/></sd-panel></fig></article>